The paper deals with the problem of domain adaptation of classification algorithms, which is a common topic in machine learning and computer vision. The use of deep Q-learning also suggests a focus on reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence. The experiments involve visual classifiers, indicating a potential focus on computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of natural language processing techniques in some of the experiments suggests a possible connection to cs.CL (Computation and Language), and the use of deep learning suggests a possible connection to cs.DL (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
